  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lowdisc_sobolskip</refname><refpurpose>Skip elements in the Sobol sequence.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>



<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>skip :</term>
      <listitem><para> a 1 x 1 matrix of floating point integers, the number of elements to discard</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>dim_num :</term>
      <listitem><para> a 1 x 1 matrix of floating point integers, the number of dimensions</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>lastq :</term>
      <listitem><para> a dim_num x 1 matrix of floating point integers, the numerators of the last vector generated</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>count :</term>
      <listitem><para> a 1 x 1 matrix of floating point integers, the index of the element in the sequence</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
The only difference with lowdisc_sobolnext is that we do not generate the
vector quasi.
   </para>
   <para>
This routine is designed to be used with the lowdisc_sobolnext() and lowdisc_sobolstart()
functions.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

